  />
  <div style="flex: 1; min-width: 300px;">
    <p>From regal estates to gritty streets, Netflix has captured all shades of London. Below are 5 hand-picked locations, with scenes and addresses for fans and tourists alike.</p>

    <p>Expect iconic moments from *The Crown*, *Top Boy*, *Enola Holmes*, and more — with exact waypoints and tips to explore them in person.</p>

    <p>We’ve even included a custom map to help you plan your walk-through of Netflix’s London universe.</p>
  </div>
</div>

### 1. The Crown — Lancaster House

<figure style="margin: 30px 0;">
  <img 
    src="https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcS7DVJBus36QzyBFO5Wp_ko-pQADyv6kM3Aag&s" 
    alt="Lancaster House representing Buckingham Palace in The Crown"
    style="width: 100%; border-radius: 8px;"
  />
  <figcaption style="text-align: center; font-style: italic; margin-top: 8px;">
    Lancaster House, often used as a Buckingham Palace stand-in
  </figcaption>
</figure>

**Waypoint:** [Lancaster House, Stable Yard, St. James’s, SW1A 1BB](https://goo.gl/maps/wEQKZTxEAxxQtYy58)

Lancaster House serves as the on-screen Buckingham Palace in *The Crown*. The historic grandeur of this estate perfectly matches royal scenes from multiple seasons.

**Tip:** While not open to the general public, it’s located right next to St. James’s Park — great for photo ops and royal fans.

### 2. Enola Holmes — Old Royal Naval College

**Waypoint:** [King William Walk, Greenwich SE10 9NN](https://goo.gl/maps/XU5g6VuwhQzHHL6w6)

Used for several bustling street scenes, this architectural gem is a period film favorite — and not just in *Enola Holmes*. Fans will recognize it from *Les Misérables*, too.

### 3. Bridgerton — Ranger’s House

**Waypoint:** [Chesterfield Walk, London SE10 8QX](https://goo.gl/maps/hmDN29zGsFzW9wXv6)

The Bridgerton family’s home is none other than Greenwich’s Ranger’s House. The stately red-brick mansion is a hidden gem and open to the public.

### 4. Luther — Southbank Skatepark

**Waypoint:** [Belvedere Rd, London SE1 8XT](https://goo.gl/maps/2zUNddg2ogz9TRzV7)

DCI John Luther often walks this gritty part of central London. The skatepark and surrounding walkways appear across multiple episodes — very atmospheric at night.

### 5. Top Boy — Samuda Estate (aka Summerhouse)

**Waypoint:** [Stebondale St, London E14 3BJ](https://goo.gl/maps/z9YzpUn13bRmA2Lf9)

This East London housing estate is where the heart of *Top Boy* beats. While raw and real, it’s best to visit during the day and respectfully.

